userPromptTemplate:
Canonical question: {{question}}
Expected SQL: {{sql}}

Generate {{count}} alternative phrasings of the canonical question. Each must mean the same thing (same expected SQL output) but vary the surface naturally — the kinds of variation real users actually produce. For each paraphrase, attach a short free-form label (1-3 words) summarising what you varied (e.g. "formal", "casual", "typo", "arabic", "bracket-list", "plus-separator", "code-mixed", or anything else that fits). Use the label that best describes the variation — you choose, no fixed vocabulary.

Return JSON EXACTLY this shape:
{
  "paraphrases": [
    { "question": "...", "label": "<short tag>", "language": "en|ar|mixed" }
  ]
}
